{
  "text": "Interleukin-21 can offer theoretical advantages for the expansion of NK cells. The temporal exposure of IL-2/IL-15-stimulated NK cells to IL-21 determines the extent to which NK-cell proliferation and function are promoted [CITATION_1] ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "35066955"
